node.text:
Katie McRose, 26, and her wife Darian travel around Texas to sheer sheep, llamas and alpacas. They founded their business, Right Choice Shearing, in 2019. This year, they expect to bring in at least $80,000 servicing over 575 farms. 

Read more: https://cnb.cx/3AfkSJ2

node.title: Bringing in $80K a year shearing sheep in Texas.

node.text:
While pursuing his dreams, 'Bling Empire's Kevin Kreider says he racked up as much as $26,000 in credit card debt. 

Luckily, the frugal star adjusted his lifestyle so he could have a fresh start in Los Angeles. Here's how he did it.

node.title: How 'Bling Empire's Kevin Kreider paid off $26,000 in debt

node.text:
About half of the U.S. population is fully vaccinated, but according to esteemed epidemiologist Larry Brilliant, that's not nearly enough to end the situation. ⁠
⁠
In fact, the world is "closer to the beginning than we are to the end," Brilliant told CNBC.⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, we're sharing 4 strategies to help you cope with the mental toll of a worsening pandemic.

node.text: This 65-year-old pays $420 per month for her two-bedroom apartment in Mexico… and yes, it’s just steps away from the beach. 🌴 Take a look inside. 👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 13, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Does a job seem too good to be true? 3 ways to detect if it is, during and after the interview #make'.

node.text:
Ever left a job interview feeling like the position was just too good to be true? 🤔⁠
⁠
It's important to be vigilant during an interview so you don't accept a position only to be disappointed by it later. We're sharing 3 ways to know for sure at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 13, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, sky and text that says 'These are the 5 traits that set extraordinary people apart, says former FBI agent 'but you need the entire set' #makeit'.

node.text:
What makes someone extraordinary? Surprisingly, the qualities that make these people stand out aren't related to their level of education, income or talents, a former FBI agent says. ⁠
⁠
From self-mastery to communication, check out the 5 traits of extraordinary people, in the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'NASA wants to pay you to live in a Mars simulation for a year #makeit'.

node.text:
NASA is looking to hire four people to participate in a yearlong program at the Johnson Space Center in Houston. Selected crew members will live together in a 1,700 square-foot facility, meant to simulate the experience of living on Mars. 🚀⁠
⁠
Think you've got what it takes? Check out the link in our bio for details on how to apply. 👩‍🚀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Netflix co-founder on building business skills: 'Don't read a book' do this amakeit'.

node.text: Marc Randolph, who co-founded Netflix with Reed Hastings, has some simple advice for those looking to develop new business skills: “Don’t read a book,” Randolph says. “Don’t take an online course.”⁠ He explains why, in the link in bio.⁠

node.text: Billionaire Ray Dalio talks about the importance of making mistakes.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '5 obvious things 'too many people' forget to do before job interviews, according to CEO of 10 years #makeit'.

node.text:
No matter how many job interviews you've been on, or how well you think on your feet, most people are rarely as prepared as they should be.⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, the CEO of a recruiting firm is sharing 5 obvious things people forget to do before a big job interview. 😬

buttons.text: Visit the COVID-19 Information Center for vaccine resources.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Feel weird asking a coworker about their vaccination status? 5 ways to start a conversation #makeit'.

node.text:
Entering a space where there is a mix of vaccinated and potentially unvaccinated people comes with risks, even for those who are vaccinated. ⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, we're sharing 5 conversation-starters that may help you open the door to talking about vaccination in the workplace.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'These are the 5 most in-demand cryptocurrency jobs right now, according to Monster #makeit'.

node.text:
To determine where cryptocurrency hiring is happening most, researchers at Monster scoured several job search platforms to identify which roles had the most new postings featuring "cryptocurrency" or "blockchain" in their descriptions. ⁠
⁠
Check out the link in our bio for the top 5 in-demand cryptocurrency jobs companies are hiring for right now.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Not all self-help books work but these 8 will actually rewire the way you think live and do your job U #make'.

node.text:
With so much of our lives being spent at home these days, now is the perfect time to self-reflect and become the best versions of ourselves.⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, we're sharing 8 books that will actually teach you how to think smarter, live better and have healthier relationships.
